body:
I was wondering if it was possible (and the level of effort needed) to support module level property statements, rather than just inline properties within an `assert property ()` block. I did some initial searching and didn't find any other issue, but I believe this is the relevant area within the parser: https://github.com/verilator/verilator/blame/master/src/verilog.y#L5248

I'm not sure whether the logic needed for the commented out section is already there as I am not familiar with the structure of the project yet. I have a minimal testcase and the resulting error here:
```sv
module testcase (
  input var clk,
  input var rst_n
);
  logic a;
  always_ff @(posedge clk or negedge rst_n)
    if (!rst_n) a <= 0;
    else a = ~a;
  property pr_001;
    @(posedge clk) !rst_n |-> !a;
  endproperty
endmodule
```
```bash
$ verilator --lint-only testcase.sv 
%Error: testcase.sv:9:3: syntax error, unexpected property
    9 |   property pr_001;
      |   ^~~~~~~~
%Error: Cannot continue
```
